                      <span>2003-01-19</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a nice little book on a very specific topic. In my opinion the author spend too much time (actually half of the book) revisiting basic concepts that any PHP developer should know pretty well, still he manages to provide very interesting information on topics that you hardly find covered elsewhere, like integrating PHP with COM, .NET, ADO or Active Directory</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">What a great book for PHP beginners</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
